Introduction

This is a notebook for the first pilot experiment of our (Kara, Ellen, and Derek) first pilot experiment examining vaccine theories using multiple attitude measures. We recruited 100 participants and lost 6 to comprehension checks, leaving 94.

Item Correlations

Heres a correlation matrix for all individual items. It appears items of some scales are intercorrelating well, though others are weaker. There is also considerable correlation among items across scalesas we might expect.

library(corrplot)
library(viridis)
corrplot(cor(df_main),
         tl.cex=.65,
         tl.col="black",
         method="color",
         col=viridis(128))

Heres another matrix, this time sorted according to a hierarchical clustering algorithm, with bounding rectangles identifying clusters. Whereas we treated these as 15 different scales, this finds just 3 separate clusters. I dont think this is a problemwe expected and even hoped these scales would be correlated with one another.

corrplot(cor(df_main[,all_items]),
         order="hclust",
         # addrect=3,
         tl.cex=.65,
         tl.col="black",
         method="color",
         col=viridis(128))
